{
  "texts": [
    "While in the desired logits vector z LLM, element z LLM (j) should be positively related to the classification probability of c t,j so that σ z LLM /δ, the output of the softmax layer, can be a probability vector.",
    "Therefore, we need to further transform vector V to make its elements positively related to the classification probability.",
    "One possible way is to inverse the elements in V, i.e., z LLM (j) = 1/V (j).",
    "C. Adaptive Weight AssignmentIn Eq.",
    "( 2), α, β, and χ denote the weights of L 0, L t-1 KD, and L LLM KD, respectively."
  ]
}